WEBVTT

1
00:01:21.750 --> 00:01:23.208
Captain. where are you?

2
00:01:23.667 --> 00:01:25.708
I'm heading there
with my sister's family.

3
00:01:26.250 --> 00:01:27.917
We're almost there. so hang on.

4
00:01:32.250 --> 00:01:33.833
Is this the right way?

5
00:01:34.042 --> 00:01:35.958
I drove through
here dozens of times.

6
00:01:36.625 --> 00:01:38.458
All the other roads
would be packed with cars.

7
00:01:45.833 --> 00:01:46.958
Oh...

8
00:01:50.167 --> 00:01:52.542
Please give us a ride.

9
00:01:53.292 --> 00:01:54.667
I have a little girl.

10
00:01:55.083 --> 00:01:56.375
I have a wife too.

11
00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:58.958
Please take us to the port.

12
00:02:00.500 --> 00:02:01.833
I'm begging you...

13
00:02:01.917 --> 00:02:04.333
I wasn't bitten!
It's not a bite!

14
00:02:09.458 --> 00:02:13.000
If we look dangerous. at
least take our girl. Please.

15
00:02:13.083 --> 00:02:14.625
Sir?

16
00:02:15.333 --> 00:02:17.542
Please! I'm begging you!

17
00:02:18.292 --> 00:02:19.458
Sir! Please!

18
00:02:22.875 --> 00:02:24.042
Jung-seok...

19
00:02:25.583 --> 00:02:27.263
Don't say anything
until we're on the ship!

20
00:02:34.667 --> 00:02:35.667
Can you tell us

21
00:02:35.750 --> 00:02:37.958
why this dreadful
virus has spread. Paul?

22
00:02:38.375 --> 00:02:39.458
Well. unfortunately.

23
00:02:39.542 --> 00:02:40.792
we don't have much information

24
00:02:40.875 --> 00:02:42.434
other than the fact
that it started out of

25
00:02:42.458 --> 00:02:44.417
a bio-factory in South Korea.

26
00:02:44.500 --> 00:02:45.667
Uh. it's unclear exactly

27
00:02:45.750 --> 00:02:49.125
how this unidentified virus
initially began to spread.

28
00:02:49.792 --> 00:02:53.042
Of course. sheer pandemonium
broke loose in South Korea.

29
00:02:53.375 --> 00:02:55.625
And many people
began to believe a rumor

30
00:02:55.708 --> 00:02:57.042
that was circulating online

31
00:02:57.125 --> 00:02:59.375
about a safe region
somewhere further down south...

32
00:02:59.458 --> 00:03:01.875
Busan? Is this the
correct pronunciation?

33
00:03:01.958 --> 00:03:04.083
That's right. And people
were evacuated there.

34
00:03:04.167 --> 00:03:07.042
But in the end. no
place was truly safe.

35
00:03:07.125 --> 00:03:09.375
But there is an
absolute safe place

36
00:03:09.458 --> 00:03:10.833
on the Korean Peninsula.

37
00:03:10.917 --> 00:03:13.875
That's correct. I believe
you're referring to North Korea.

38
00:03:14.458 --> 00:03:16.125
Perhaps it's fortunate
that this happened

39
00:03:16.208 --> 00:03:17.708
before the reunification!

40
00:03:17.792 --> 00:03:19.042
So it turns out.

41
00:03:19.375 --> 00:03:23.000
So how long before the Korean
government lost all control?

42
00:03:23.083 --> 00:03:24.625
Just one day.

43
00:03:26.917 --> 00:03:29.292
Please move slowly!

44
00:03:29.792 --> 00:03:31.625
This is Alpha One.

45
00:03:32.792 --> 00:03:33.792
Move on!

46
00:03:33.875 --> 00:03:34.875
Be careful!

47
00:03:48.833 --> 00:03:49.875
This is Alpha Two.

48
00:03:49.958 --> 00:03:51.838
We have about 50
civilians waiting for boarding.

49
00:04:07.958 --> 00:04:09.042
Uncle.

50
00:04:12.750 --> 00:04:13.958
Are you all right. Dong-hwan?

51
00:04:14.375 --> 00:04:15.375
Yes.

52
00:04:16.042 --> 00:04:17.042
Where's Chul-min?

53
00:04:17.458 --> 00:04:19.375
He went to get some relief aid.

54
00:04:20.333 --> 00:04:24.458
But shouldn't we have
arrived in Japan by now?

55
00:04:25.417 --> 00:04:27.583
I'm sure we're almost
there. don't worry.

56
00:04:29.125 --> 00:04:30.125
Captain!

57
00:04:33.875 --> 00:04:34.875
What is it?

58
00:04:34.958 --> 00:04:36.917
We're being rerouted
to Hong Kong.

59
00:04:38.250 --> 00:04:39.250
Why all of sudden?

60
00:04:39.583 --> 00:04:41.083
They're not telling me why.

61
00:04:43.458 --> 00:04:44.833
I have to go check something.

62
00:04:57.958 --> 00:04:59.083
Excuse me.

63
00:05:01.250 --> 00:05:03.333
I'll ask about it. so go
and check what's going on.

64
00:05:03.417 --> 00:05:04.417
Yes. sir.

65
00:05:05.042 --> 00:05:06.083
Excuse me.

66
00:05:06.500 --> 00:05:07.500
Excuse me.

67
00:05:14.208 --> 00:05:15.208
Uh.

68
00:05:44.250 --> 00:05:45.292
Sir!

69
00:05:46.667 --> 00:05:47.667
Sir!

70
00:05:47.958 --> 00:05:50.083
Is it true that we are
rerouting to Hong Kong?

71
00:05:50.167 --> 00:05:51.958
Please return to your seats.

72
00:05:52.458 --> 00:05:54.542
We need to understand
the situation. sir!

73
00:05:55.417 --> 00:05:56.917
Everyone's getting nervous.

74
00:05:57.208 --> 00:06:00.583
Please return to your seat
and await further instructions.

75
00:06:00.875 --> 00:06:01.708
Sir!

76
00:06:01.833 --> 00:06:02.833
We have a problem.

77
00:06:02.917 --> 00:06:05.208
We've found an infected
person on the lower deck cabins.

78
00:06:06.792 --> 00:06:07.792
We get ramen too?

79
00:06:10.333 --> 00:06:12.042
Come in. Leave your bag here.

80
00:06:12.125 --> 00:06:13.125
It looks good.

81
00:06:13.292 --> 00:06:14.292
Please come in.

82
00:06:14.750 --> 00:06:16.083
- Infected!
- What?

83
00:06:20.750 --> 00:06:21.792
What is it?

84
00:07:17.208 --> 00:07:18.958
It's okay. I'll be right here.

85
00:07:19.458 --> 00:07:22.875
Breathe. Dong-hwan.
I'm not going anywhere.

86
00:07:23.375 --> 00:07:24.542
It'll be okay.

87
00:07:24.792 --> 00:07:26.625
Look at me.

88
00:07:30.375 --> 00:07:33.500
I'll be right here with you.

89
00:07:37.583 --> 00:07:40.042
What do I do?

90
00:07:41.792 --> 00:07:44.208
Your uncle's here. Dong-hwan.

91
00:07:48.583 --> 00:07:49.583
Sis...

92
00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:51.958
- What do we do?
- We have to go.

93
00:07:52.042 --> 00:07:53.375
We have to go now. come on!

94
00:07:54.917 --> 00:07:56.708
- Let's go!
- Your uncle...

95
00:07:58.500 --> 00:07:59.542
We have to go!

96
00:08:00.833 --> 00:08:01.958
We must leave.

97
00:08:02.042 --> 00:08:03.042
Come on!

98
00:08:04.875 --> 00:08:05.917
Sis!

99
00:08:23.417 --> 00:08:25.625
Sis! Sis!

100
00:08:40.125 --> 00:08:41.167
Honey!

101
00:08:42.500 --> 00:08:43.500
No!

102
00:09:18.250 --> 00:09:20.750
There is even a
case of infected hosts

103
00:09:20.833 --> 00:09:22.375
that were found
on the last lifeboats

104
00:09:22.458 --> 00:09:23.708
to leave for Hong Kong.

105
00:09:23.792 --> 00:09:25.458
After that. the
neighboring countries

106
00:09:25.542 --> 00:09:28.708
decided to no longer
accept any more refugees.

107
00:09:28.792 --> 00:09:31.625
In effect. Korea became
completely quarantined.

108
00:09:31.792 --> 00:09:33.792
Yes. it's been
four years already.

109
00:09:33.875 --> 00:09:35.583
Yes. Four years.

110
00:10:42.458 --> 00:10:43.667
Wake him up.

111
00:10:48.208 --> 00:10:50.667
Hey! Wake up!

112
00:10:55.125 --> 00:10:56.167
That's enough!

113
00:10:59.542 --> 00:11:01.083
We are not here to fight.

114
00:11:01.500 --> 00:11:02.917
The boss wants to see you.

115
00:11:06.375 --> 00:11:07.375
Hey!

116
00:11:42.000 --> 00:11:43.000
Come on.

117
00:11:51.208 --> 00:11:52.458
What are you doing here?

118
00:11:52.708 --> 00:11:53.708
Let's leave.

119
00:11:53.792 --> 00:11:54.792
Let go of me.

120
00:11:55.458 --> 00:11:56.458
Hyung!

121
00:11:56.583 --> 00:11:57.583
"Hyung."

122
00:11:59.625 --> 00:12:01.167
It means "brother." doesn't it?

123
00:12:01.375 --> 00:12:02.750
You two brothers? Huh?

124
00:12:03.000 --> 00:12:04.167
No. no. no.

125
00:12:04.250 --> 00:12:06.458
He is my dead wife's brother.

126
00:12:06.833 --> 00:12:08.042
Not brother.

127
00:12:09.042 --> 00:12:11.042
That sounds like
a real tragic story.

128
00:12:13.083 --> 00:12:14.125
Have a seat.

129
00:12:14.708 --> 00:12:16.393
I don't know what the
hell is it with you people

130
00:12:16.417 --> 00:12:18.083
from the peninsula? You. uh...

131
00:12:18.708 --> 00:12:19.958
have an air about you.

132
00:12:20.542 --> 00:12:22.792
You have a lot
of sad. sad tales...

133
00:12:23.250 --> 00:12:25.208
Let's get down to business.

134
00:12:25.667 --> 00:12:28.542
Should I say "your
country" or "the peninsula"?

135
00:12:29.125 --> 00:12:31.167
Look. I. I heard a rumor...

136
00:12:31.625 --> 00:12:35.042
There seems to be some
people that are going back down

137
00:12:35.125 --> 00:12:38.417
into the peninsula to
make their own fate.

138
00:12:39.250 --> 00:12:42.500
Zombies don't give a damn
about all that gold and money.

139
00:12:42.583 --> 00:12:45.542
which is just laying
around there unguarded.

140
00:12:46.333 --> 00:12:47.875
I think it's ingenious.

141
00:12:47.958 --> 00:12:49.000
Wow.

142
00:12:50.375 --> 00:12:51.792
You want us to go back in there?

143
00:12:52.875 --> 00:12:54.375
Have you lost your mind?

144
00:12:55.083 --> 00:12:56.292
My brother.

145
00:12:57.042 --> 00:13:00.083
my mind is completely
sound. thank you.

146
00:13:00.375 --> 00:13:01.375
Okay.

147
00:13:01.958 --> 00:13:03.000
So...

148
00:13:03.958 --> 00:13:06.375
the neighboring countries
around the peninsula

149
00:13:06.458 --> 00:13:08.292
are controlling
every ship and plane

150
00:13:08.375 --> 00:13:09.625
that crosses the border.

151
00:13:10.667 --> 00:13:12.667
How would you get in or out?

152
00:13:13.792 --> 00:13:15.042
It's been done.

153
00:13:15.500 --> 00:13:17.833
You don't need to worry
about the coast guard.

154
00:13:18.583 --> 00:13:20.292
As long as we keep paying them.

155
00:13:20.375 --> 00:13:22.667
the ships go in.
the ships go out.

156
00:13:23.250 --> 00:13:24.250
As a matter of fact.

157
00:13:24.333 --> 00:13:26.792
technically. we had
the money and the truck.

158
00:13:27.417 --> 00:13:29.167
Twenty million dollars.

159
00:13:29.250 --> 00:13:30.833
Until we went
missing halfway here.

160
00:13:30.917 --> 00:13:32.167
Where was the last time we...

161
00:13:32.250 --> 00:13:33.500
On the Omok Bridge.

162
00:13:33.625 --> 00:13:34.625
Mok-dong?

163
00:13:35.708 --> 00:13:36.708
What?

164
00:13:36.792 --> 00:13:38.309
Look. I don't think
it's too difficult.

165
00:13:38.333 --> 00:13:39.917
You just go in at night.

166
00:13:40.000 --> 00:13:42.417
you get the truck. come
back with the money.

167
00:13:42.500 --> 00:13:45.125
and don't worry
about those zombies.

168
00:13:45.208 --> 00:13:47.875
I hear they are
practically blind at night.

169
00:13:48.417 --> 00:13:49.500
So...

170
00:13:50.542 --> 00:13:52.458
How much money we get?

171
00:13:55.375 --> 00:13:57.333
Well. that's the
question. isn't it?

172
00:13:57.750 --> 00:13:58.750
Half.

173
00:13:59.708 --> 00:14:02.708
That is. if you come back alive.

174
00:14:03.583 --> 00:14:07.500
That's 2.5 million
dollars per head.

175
00:14:08.500 --> 00:14:09.708
Now listen to me.

176
00:14:09.875 --> 00:14:12.667
You have no idea when or even

177
00:14:12.875 --> 00:14:16.500
if the government is
ever going to grant you

178
00:14:16.583 --> 00:14:17.958
any refugee status.

179
00:14:18.042 --> 00:14:21.333
so you might as well make
your own goddamn future.

180
00:14:21.417 --> 00:14:22.417
Think!

181
00:14:33.875 --> 00:14:38.000
We just have to hop on a
boat. and bring the truck back.

182
00:14:38.083 --> 00:14:39.417
What's so hard about that?

183
00:14:39.875 --> 00:14:41.500
It'll only take half a day.

184
00:14:46.458 --> 00:14:49.167
Are you nuts? You
want to go back there?

185
00:14:52.417 --> 00:14:53.809
Then do you want
to keep living here.

186
00:14:53.833 --> 00:14:54.873
getting treated like scum?

187
00:14:59.375 --> 00:15:02.458
You should have let me
die with my son and wife!

188
00:15:02.958 --> 00:15:04.125
Why did you do it?

189
00:15:05.125 --> 00:15:06.625
Had I let you die.

190
00:15:07.125 --> 00:15:08.708
everyone on that
ship would've died.

191
00:15:08.958 --> 00:15:09.958
Am I wrong?

192
00:15:12.042 --> 00:15:13.458
It was a sensible decision.

193
00:15:15.333 --> 00:15:17.125
Sensible decision. my ass.

194
00:15:18.875 --> 00:15:20.125
Did you even try?

195
00:15:22.750 --> 00:15:23.792
Jung-seok...

196
00:15:25.208 --> 00:15:26.875
You're tormented too!

197
00:15:28.792 --> 00:15:30.500
You just gave up!

198
00:15:34.958 --> 00:15:37.542
Whatever. forget it.

199
00:15:37.875 --> 00:15:38.875
Okay.

200
00:15:39.958 --> 00:15:42.875
Well. I'm going to go there.

201
00:15:42.958 --> 00:15:46.458
so you can do whatever you want.

202
00:15:47.208 --> 00:15:49.625
Let's just not bump
into each other.

203
00:15:50.458 --> 00:15:51.917
It's hard for both of us.

204
00:15:52.625 --> 00:15:54.208
Bye-bye. Bye-bye.

205
00:15:54.875 --> 00:15:56.083
Aren't they bastards

206
00:15:56.167 --> 00:15:57.458
from the peninsula?

207
00:15:57.542 --> 00:15:59.750
- What?
- Where the virus came from!

208
00:16:00.250 --> 00:16:02.375
Should you be
letting them in here?

209
00:16:02.458 --> 00:16:03.458
Move aside.

210
00:16:04.083 --> 00:16:04.792
- Let go of me.
- Stop.

211
00:16:04.875 --> 00:16:06.226
Do you even care
about the others?

212
00:16:06.250 --> 00:16:07.083
Stop it.

213
00:16:07.167 --> 00:16:09.708
Is he infected?

214
00:16:09.792 --> 00:16:11.292
Come on. Stop.

215
00:16:11.625 --> 00:16:13.583
I won't take your
money. so just leave!

216
00:16:15.125 --> 00:16:16.125
You go ahead.

217
00:16:49.417 --> 00:16:51.332
You're entering the
peninsula waters.

218
00:16:51.333 --> 00:16:52.708
Turn back.

219
00:16:52.917 --> 00:16:54.832
You're entering the
peninsula waters.

220
00:16:54.833 --> 00:16:55.833
Turn back.

221
00:16:55.834 --> 00:16:58.917
This is Z055 Chungpyung.

222
00:17:01.542 --> 00:17:02.375
Hello?

223
00:17:02.458 --> 00:17:06.125
It's all good if
there's no response.

224
00:17:28.292 --> 00:17:29.750
Almost there!

225
00:17:32.667 --> 00:17:34.958
No need to be so serious.

226
00:17:35.042 --> 00:17:37.042
Soon. you'll be rich!

227
00:17:37.750 --> 00:17:39.000
Take what you need.

228
00:17:39.875 --> 00:17:42.750
Don't forget. the
zombies are blind at night

229
00:17:42.833 --> 00:17:44.208
and sensitive to sound.

230
00:17:45.083 --> 00:17:46.458
And the important thing.

231
00:17:47.000 --> 00:17:48.083
We'll drop you off

232
00:17:48.125 --> 00:17:52.042
and stay at sea
nearby for three days.

233
00:17:56.583 --> 00:17:57.667
Take these.

234
00:17:58.625 --> 00:17:59.625
One for you.

235
00:18:00.083 --> 00:18:02.208
And...

236
00:18:02.458 --> 00:18:03.458
another.

237
00:18:04.458 --> 00:18:06.625
Call me when you get
to the port with the truck

238
00:18:06.708 --> 00:18:08.667
and we'll pull up the boat.

239
00:18:13.292 --> 00:18:14.542
And lastly!

240
00:18:15.083 --> 00:18:18.583
You escaped out of there
alive. so you know better...

241
00:18:19.125 --> 00:18:22.375
Don't screw up trying to
save each other for nothing.

242
00:18:22.833 --> 00:18:24.792
Don't worry. We know.

243
00:18:25.208 --> 00:18:26.208
Great!

244
00:18:26.875 --> 00:18:28.042
Do not let us down.

245
00:18:37.417 --> 00:18:40.875
It makes me nervous that
you two know each other.

246
00:18:40.958 --> 00:18:42.333
I know.

247
00:18:43.083 --> 00:18:45.125
We have to pull this
off no matter what.

248
00:18:45.208 --> 00:18:46.518
so don't let your
personal emotions

249
00:18:46.542 --> 00:18:47.542
get mixed up in the way.

250
00:18:47.917 --> 00:18:49.517
We won't even see
each other after this.

251
00:18:50.083 --> 00:18:51.208
so don't worry.

252
00:18:52.583 --> 00:18:53.625
Fine.

253
00:18:54.167 --> 00:18:55.250
Whatever. man.

254
00:20:20.333 --> 00:20:27.292
GOD HAS FORSAKEN US

255
00:20:47.833 --> 00:20:49.167
We're not on a tour. you know.

256
00:20:50.083 --> 00:20:53.208
Let's hurry things along. we
should leave before sunrise.

257
00:20:54.083 --> 00:20:55.750
All right. let's
get it over with.

258
00:20:55.833 --> 00:20:57.333
Jeez.

259
00:21:02.208 --> 00:21:03.333
Is it working?

260
00:21:05.833 --> 00:21:07.208
Nice!

261
00:21:28.333 --> 00:21:30.417
It's unrecognizable
now. My goodness.

262
00:21:30.917 --> 00:21:33.792
The city became a
ruin in just four years.

263
00:21:34.542 --> 00:21:35.833
Did you live near here?

264
00:21:36.833 --> 00:21:39.708
I used to drive a cab.

265
00:21:40.208 --> 00:21:42.875
So I pretty much
know all the roads.

266
00:21:44.125 --> 00:21:46.750
At the very least. those jerks
put together a good team.

267
00:21:57.792 --> 00:21:59.750
A HEALTHY. CAREFREE COUNTRY

268
00:22:22.667 --> 00:22:23.917
Could that be it?

269
00:22:24.000 --> 00:22:25.333
Where?

270
00:22:26.792 --> 00:22:28.625
The plate number is 6431. right?

271
00:22:29.208 --> 00:22:30.417
We'll find out soon.

272
00:22:31.000 --> 00:22:32.917
You stay here. I'll go alone.

273
00:22:33.000 --> 00:22:34.042
What?

274
00:22:34.125 --> 00:22:36.000
Hey. hey. hey! Wait!

275
00:23:42.292 --> 00:23:43.542
Come on. come on. come on!

276
00:23:44.583 --> 00:23:45.958
What's with you?

277
00:23:46.792 --> 00:23:47.958
Is that the truck?

278
00:23:48.708 --> 00:23:49.833
No. it isn't.

279
00:23:51.542 --> 00:23:53.667
It should be nearby. Let's
look around a bit more.

280
00:24:21.542 --> 00:24:23.958
There. I see one more.

281
00:24:25.833 --> 00:24:27.167
Let's check it out.

282
00:24:28.333 --> 00:24:29.583
Okay.

283
00:24:48.417 --> 00:24:52.124
I'll go have a look.
You stay here.

284
00:24:52.125 --> 00:24:53.333
Stop it!

285
00:24:53.750 --> 00:24:55.042
I'm not on a tour. you know.

286
00:24:55.833 --> 00:24:56.958
We'll go together.

287
00:24:57.542 --> 00:24:58.542
Mister.

288
00:24:58.792 --> 00:25:00.833
Let's take a look.

289
00:25:22.167 --> 00:25:23.542
Are they Unit 631?

290
00:25:24.958 --> 00:25:25.958
No.

291
00:25:26.792 --> 00:25:27.792
They're not.

292
00:25:29.833 --> 00:25:31.750
Jackpot. we found it.

293
00:25:57.417 --> 00:25:58.500
It was true...

294
00:26:01.875 --> 00:26:03.875
What they said was true.

295
00:26:03.958 --> 00:26:06.083
It's all in US dollars.
How much is all this?

296
00:26:06.917 --> 00:26:08.667
We confirmed it.
so let's get going.

297
00:26:10.750 --> 00:26:11.750
Okay.

298
00:26:13.083 --> 00:26:14.083
Jeez.

299
00:26:15.917 --> 00:26:16.917
Hey!

300
00:26:17.333 --> 00:26:18.542
Over here!

301
00:26:21.000 --> 00:26:24.083
He must've been the last
person to make contact.

302
00:26:26.208 --> 00:26:28.208
How unfortunate.

303
00:26:28.625 --> 00:26:30.625
He could've been a millionaire.

304
00:26:31.042 --> 00:26:32.874
But it's good for us.

305
00:26:32.875 --> 00:26:34.750
Let's pull him out and go.

306
00:26:36.750 --> 00:26:39.250
Oh. jeez...

307
00:26:40.250 --> 00:26:41.458
He stinks...

308
00:26:43.167 --> 00:26:45.583
Move your leg. Thank you.

309
00:26:45.833 --> 00:26:47.125
Thank you.

310
00:26:57.500 --> 00:26:58.792
Idiots.

311
00:27:08.417 --> 00:27:09.458
Are you okay?

312
00:27:09.917 --> 00:27:11.833
I'm fine. I wasn't bitten.

313
00:27:19.792 --> 00:27:22.417
Gosh. what are they up to?

314
00:27:36.875 --> 00:27:38.333
Get in the car. go!

315
00:27:41.125 --> 00:27:42.208
Back it up!

316
00:28:33.250 --> 00:28:34.500
Hurry. hurry. hurry!

317
00:28:34.583 --> 00:28:35.625
Come on. come on. come on!

318
00:28:35.708 --> 00:28:36.792
All right!

319
00:28:38.583 --> 00:28:39.583
Let's go!

320
00:28:49.000 --> 00:28:50.167
We're clear. we're clear!

321
00:28:50.375 --> 00:28:51.500
Thank you...

322
00:28:52.417 --> 00:28:55.000
So the money's really there?

323
00:28:56.042 --> 00:28:58.042
You're a millionaire!

324
00:29:00.250 --> 00:29:01.292
Yes!

325
00:29:01.375 --> 00:29:03.000
Awesome!

326
00:29:03.375 --> 00:29:04.708
What will you do with the money?

327
00:29:04.792 --> 00:29:06.250
Me? Uh...

328
00:29:06.333 --> 00:29:07.458
Maybe I'll hire a chauffeur.

329
00:29:07.542 --> 00:29:09.292
Like a real millionaire!

330
00:29:13.208 --> 00:29:15.328
So we just have to get to
the harbor and call them in.

331
00:29:16.667 --> 00:29:18.583
This is a piece of cake!

332
00:29:20.542 --> 00:29:21.750
Give me the satellite phone.

333
00:29:21.833 --> 00:29:23.542
Huh? Sure. hold on.

334
00:29:35.583 --> 00:29:36.583
Here.

335
00:29:39.750 --> 00:29:41.000
What's that?

336
00:30:02.042 --> 00:30:03.083
Just drive!

337
00:30:03.292 --> 00:30:05.083
Go. go. go! Just go!

338
00:31:51.292 --> 00:31:52.542
Hop in. if you want to live.

339
00:31:58.833 --> 00:31:59.875
Sorry!

340
00:32:27.458 --> 00:32:28.833
You must've been scared.

341
00:32:29.833 --> 00:32:34.125
Yu-jin. I told you not to
act so friendly to strangers.

342
00:32:35.292 --> 00:32:36.500
Sit back properly.

343
00:34:26.667 --> 00:34:28.083
Dang. he passed out.

344
00:34:28.917 --> 00:34:30.750
Did I not tell him to buckle up?

345
00:34:35.333 --> 00:34:38.083
Joon-i. can you
drive through them?

346
00:34:40.208 --> 00:34:41.250
I'm not sure.

347
00:34:42.292 --> 00:34:45.125
Then what? Do I
need to get involved?

348
00:35:34.000 --> 00:35:35.208
Ooh...

349
00:35:35.292 --> 00:35:36.667
Ooh.

350
00:35:47.333 --> 00:35:48.542
Uh?

351
00:35:56.875 --> 00:35:57.958
Really?

352
00:35:58.667 --> 00:36:02.083
The ground was
weird. it wasn't my fault.

353
00:36:03.417 --> 00:36:04.917
Oh.

354
00:36:38.292 --> 00:36:39.667
I really liked that one. though.

355
00:37:06.792 --> 00:37:09.167
CITY NIGHT CLUB

356
00:37:51.167 --> 00:37:53.583
It's a grocery truck. Nice.

357
00:37:54.500 --> 00:37:55.875
It looks new.

358
00:38:00.792 --> 00:38:02.792
- Who's that?
- He's alive!

359
00:38:05.417 --> 00:38:08.167
- Please. help me...
- Be careful.

360
00:38:08.375 --> 00:38:11.958
- Be careful.
- Help me. I'm begging you...

361
00:38:15.750 --> 00:38:17.583
Help me. please.

362
00:38:17.667 --> 00:38:19.292
What the hell's going on?

363
00:38:19.792 --> 00:38:21.208
He's just an
infected. you jerks.

364
00:38:21.333 --> 00:38:22.833
Have you never seen one before?

365
00:38:23.375 --> 00:38:24.375
Please...

366
00:38:24.458 --> 00:38:26.250
It's all right. come here.

367
00:38:46.792 --> 00:38:51.417
Sir. please. help me...

368
00:38:51.958 --> 00:38:54.083
I'm begging you...

369
00:38:58.125 --> 00:39:00.208
- Give it to me.
- Here you go!

370
00:39:03.042 --> 00:39:04.417
Sir...

371
00:39:07.417 --> 00:39:09.000
Nice shot!

372
00:39:09.208 --> 00:39:10.750
Wow. he killed him properly.

373
00:39:11.542 --> 00:39:12.667
Damn it!

374
00:39:14.625 --> 00:39:16.667
It got on my pants. I
should get it washed.

375
00:39:17.333 --> 00:39:18.333
Here.

376
00:39:19.292 --> 00:39:20.750
Let's get back.
the sun will rise.

377
00:39:21.292 --> 00:39:22.292
Shit...

378
00:39:22.500 --> 00:39:25.125
- Let's go.
- The zombies are coming!

379
00:39:28.667 --> 00:39:29.667
Huh?

380
00:39:50.292 --> 00:39:51.917
You little rascals!

381
00:39:52.250 --> 00:39:53.490
You brought something dangerous

382
00:39:53.542 --> 00:39:55.500
instead of what you
were supposed to get.

383
00:39:55.625 --> 00:39:56.667
Hey!

384
00:39:57.250 --> 00:39:59.010
You'd have been locked
up for insubordination

385
00:39:59.042 --> 00:40:00.792
if it were the old days!

386
00:40:07.417 --> 00:40:08.792
Lieutenant Yoon! Captain Hwang!

387
00:40:08.875 --> 00:40:09.875
Assemble!

388
00:40:10.375 --> 00:40:11.792
Aren't you going
to make a report?

389
00:40:11.875 --> 00:40:13.375
Did you get what I asked?

390
00:40:13.667 --> 00:40:16.333
Salute! Division
commander. we did not get it!

391
00:40:18.292 --> 00:40:19.292
Hey!

392
00:40:19.625 --> 00:40:20.958
How could you not get it?

393
00:40:21.333 --> 00:40:22.374
The ROK-US Combined
Forces Command

394
00:40:22.375 --> 00:40:23.250
is waiting for my call!

395
00:40:23.333 --> 00:40:24.625
Without batteries...

396
00:40:24.833 --> 00:40:25.833
Come on!

397
00:40:25.917 --> 00:40:27.500
- Are you having fun?
- Joon-i!

398
00:40:28.042 --> 00:40:29.583
- Captain Hwang!
- Grandpa!

399
00:40:30.208 --> 00:40:32.125
How long will you go
on with that army stuff?

400
00:40:32.208 --> 00:40:33.208
Aren't you sick of it?

401
00:40:33.292 --> 00:40:34.542
No. it's for real this time!

402
00:40:34.625 --> 00:40:37.208
The newly appointed
Major Jane is totally different.

403
00:40:37.292 --> 00:40:38.917
She and I get along.

404
00:40:39.000 --> 00:40:41.958
And it seems like
we'll get rescued soon.

405
00:40:42.042 --> 00:40:44.417
Listen to me. I'm good
friends with her. so...

406
00:40:44.500 --> 00:40:46.518
- Stop it! I'm sick of it!
- Yu-jin. you believe me. right?

407
00:40:46.542 --> 00:40:47.542
Who are you?

408
00:40:50.500 --> 00:40:52.875
I guess you've never
experienced a wild dog hunt before.

409
00:40:52.958 --> 00:40:54.458
You should've
known that such trucks

410
00:40:54.542 --> 00:40:56.125
would attract their attention.

411
00:40:56.458 --> 00:40:57.542
"Truck"?

412
00:40:57.625 --> 00:40:58.958
Who's that?

413
00:40:59.042 --> 00:41:00.042
Mom!

414
00:41:05.208 --> 00:41:08.417
Sir! Please!

415
00:41:11.417 --> 00:41:14.083
He was almost
caught by Unit 631.

416
00:41:15.292 --> 00:41:16.667
You went outside again?

417
00:41:17.292 --> 00:41:19.000
I convinced her to go.

418
00:41:19.083 --> 00:41:20.667
Why don't you ever listen to me?

419
00:41:22.458 --> 00:41:23.625
I'm sorry. Mom.

420
00:41:25.375 --> 00:41:27.958
They're batteries.
Grandpa. she got batteries!

421
00:41:29.667 --> 00:41:31.583
Okay! Okay!

422
00:41:34.292 --> 00:41:35.292
They fit.

423
00:41:35.375 --> 00:41:37.375
Hi. Jane? Jane? Major Jane?

424
00:41:37.958 --> 00:41:40.500
Oh. Jane! Oh. Jane! Okay!

425
00:41:42.333 --> 00:41:43.542
Are you okay?

426
00:41:43.625 --> 00:41:46.250
- I'm okay! Yeah!
- You should turn it on.

427
00:41:46.333 --> 00:41:47.750
We are strong
soldiers! No problem!

428
00:41:47.833 --> 00:41:49.083
I'm Yu-jin!

429
00:41:51.375 --> 00:41:52.458
When are you coming?

430
00:41:52.542 --> 00:41:54.823
- So people still live here...
- They said they're coming!

431
00:41:56.583 --> 00:41:57.667
Who are you?

432
00:41:58.292 --> 00:41:59.625
Are you with Unit 631?

433
00:42:03.583 --> 00:42:05.625
I don't know what 631 is.

434
00:42:07.458 --> 00:42:09.667
I came to Incheon
by boat yesterday.

435
00:42:10.875 --> 00:42:12.042
From Hong Kong.

436
00:42:12.500 --> 00:42:13.500
What?

437
00:42:14.625 --> 00:42:16.083
From where?

438
00:42:27.292 --> 00:42:29.000
Damn. the sun is rising.

439
00:42:30.417 --> 00:42:32.083
Let's hurry up.

440
00:42:37.250 --> 00:42:38.750
The third platoon is returning!

441
00:42:38.833 --> 00:42:40.208
Open the gate!

442
00:42:49.958 --> 00:42:52.417
There are one. two. three.
four. five. six boxes of cookies.

443
00:42:52.792 --> 00:42:54.000
That's all correct.

444
00:42:56.375 --> 00:42:57.708
Scrap soup again?

445
00:42:58.000 --> 00:42:59.125
Eat if you want to live.

446
00:42:59.208 --> 00:43:02.292
That looks good.
Have a great meal!

447
00:43:02.375 --> 00:43:04.333
Have a nice meal.
Have a nice meal.

448
00:43:06.542 --> 00:43:08.167
The third platoon is back!

449
00:43:08.250 --> 00:43:09.583
They're here!

450
00:43:19.542 --> 00:43:23.250
- They're back!
- They're here!

451
00:43:24.917 --> 00:43:27.125
Great work. everyone.

452
00:43:27.208 --> 00:43:28.875
Look! Isn't it awesome?

453
00:43:28.958 --> 00:43:30.583
- Yeah!
- It sure is.

454
00:43:30.667 --> 00:43:32.292
My boys worked so hard!

455
00:43:32.375 --> 00:43:34.708
Bring us a can of
tuna. that's all I ask!

456
00:43:34.792 --> 00:43:36.059
- I'm sorry. sir...
- No. bring one.

457
00:43:36.083 --> 00:43:37.768
We were told to keep
a tight lid on supplies.

458
00:43:37.792 --> 00:43:40.250
If I keep handing out stuff.
there won't be anything left.

459
00:43:40.333 --> 00:43:41.542
And Captain Seo is...

460
00:43:42.125 --> 00:43:43.292
One can is too much?

461
00:43:43.542 --> 00:43:44.542
That's not it...

462
00:43:44.875 --> 00:43:45.875
Bring it.

463
00:43:46.125 --> 00:43:47.226
They're serving
food at the cafeteria.

464
00:43:47.250 --> 00:43:48.000
Get it!

465
00:43:48.001 --> 00:43:49.417
I said bring it!

466
00:43:49.667 --> 00:43:51.083
So I should just have scraps?

467
00:43:51.333 --> 00:43:52.375
That's not...

468
00:43:52.458 --> 00:43:53.458
Do you want it?

469
00:43:53.792 --> 00:43:55.917
I have to report to
Captain Seo first.

470
00:43:56.542 --> 00:43:58.000
Just bring it. asshole!

471
00:43:59.208 --> 00:44:03.250
Report to a guy who's
never even fought before?

472
00:44:03.667 --> 00:44:05.000
He's my commander.

473
00:44:05.083 --> 00:44:07.125
- Sergeant...
- Piss off. you bastard!

474
00:44:08.792 --> 00:44:10.542
- What was that?
- I'm talking here!

475
00:44:10.917 --> 00:44:12.417
- What was that?
- Hello?

476
00:44:12.833 --> 00:44:15.750
- Where is it coming from?
- I heard something.

477
00:44:18.750 --> 00:44:20.208
- What? A person?
- Hang on.

478
00:44:20.292 --> 00:44:22.833
Sir. we have a wild dog here.

479
00:44:23.667 --> 00:44:24.667
- What?
- Get him.

480
00:44:24.958 --> 00:44:26.250
What's a wild dog?

481
00:44:28.583 --> 00:44:29.958
Are you soldiers?

482
00:44:30.458 --> 00:44:32.833
Help me. I'm not from here.

483
00:44:33.958 --> 00:44:34.958
Get up. you bastard.

484
00:44:35.042 --> 00:44:36.500
Has the game started?

485
00:44:36.708 --> 00:44:37.750
It hasn't. sir.

486
00:44:37.833 --> 00:44:39.375
Take him to the arena.

487
00:44:39.458 --> 00:44:41.500
- Yes. sir.
- Let's go!

488
00:44:42.875 --> 00:44:44.583
We have a new player!

489
00:44:49.250 --> 00:44:53.667
Keep sucking up to Captain
Seo. and I'll kill you both.

490
00:44:53.750 --> 00:44:54.750
Got that?

491
00:44:56.750 --> 00:44:58.625
You little...

492
00:45:01.667 --> 00:45:02.792
Hey! Hey!

493
00:45:03.792 --> 00:45:05.208
He probably
wasted all the flares

494
00:45:05.292 --> 00:45:06.792
without knowing what to get.

495
00:45:07.292 --> 00:45:08.375
That idiot.

496
00:45:08.792 --> 00:45:12.583
He brought so much
useless crap last time.

497
00:45:17.583 --> 00:45:18.792
What the hell?

498
00:45:19.208 --> 00:45:21.000
We are strong soldiers!

499
00:45:21.292 --> 00:45:22.583
Strong! Strong!

500
00:45:23.500 --> 00:45:24.750
Strong. Strong.

501
00:45:26.000 --> 00:45:28.125
No one ever came to
rescue us in four years.

502
00:45:29.167 --> 00:45:30.833
but some chump
change was all it took?

503
00:45:33.750 --> 00:45:35.083
What about your group?

504
00:45:39.958 --> 00:45:41.042
They're all dead.

505
00:45:42.917 --> 00:45:44.000
Everyone.

506
00:45:46.375 --> 00:45:47.583
We got a fresh one!

507
00:46:02.125 --> 00:46:03.500
Hey there. cutie!

508
00:46:08.833 --> 00:46:10.208
Who were those soldiers?

509
00:46:10.292 --> 00:46:11.958
They're called Unit 631.

510
00:46:12.708 --> 00:46:15.188
They used to be a military unit
dispatched to rescue civilians.

511
00:46:15.500 --> 00:46:17.417
You were with them?

512
00:46:17.500 --> 00:46:19.875
We lived there
before we escaped.

513
00:46:19.958 --> 00:46:21.458
At first.

514
00:46:23.250 --> 00:46:24.809
They sent out SOS
signals for a few years.

515
00:46:24.833 --> 00:46:25.958
which were left unanswered.

516
00:46:27.167 --> 00:46:29.125
After that. they
gave up everything.

517
00:46:29.833 --> 00:46:31.333
and now they're all crazy.

518
00:46:32.500 --> 00:46:34.583
HAWAl I

519
00:47:07.333 --> 00:47:08.667
Hm.

520
00:47:09.542 --> 00:47:10.625
I'm leaving.

521
00:47:19.792 --> 00:47:20.792
Yes?

522
00:47:29.583 --> 00:47:30.583
Bang!

523
00:47:33.750 --> 00:47:36.917
Awesome. that's great.

524
00:47:41.042 --> 00:47:43.417
I'm not someone who
takes bribes. take it back.

525
00:47:43.542 --> 00:47:45.458
Gosh. you're making me sad.

526
00:47:45.542 --> 00:47:47.583
I don't take bribes!

527
00:47:47.667 --> 00:47:49.000
Look at it. it's Black Label.

528
00:47:50.125 --> 00:47:52.792
Thanks. I was
finishing my last drink.

529
00:47:53.708 --> 00:47:56.208
Here. accept my drink.

530
00:48:04.542 --> 00:48:05.875
Nothing to report again?

531
00:48:05.958 --> 00:48:07.500
No. nothing happened.

532
00:48:08.083 --> 00:48:12.583
Sergeant Hwang stole a
truck from wild dogs overnight.

533
00:48:13.125 --> 00:48:16.417
and was boasting like crazy.

534
00:48:16.500 --> 00:48:18.500
acting all high and mighty...

535
00:48:19.333 --> 00:48:22.542
So where did our
valiant sergeant go today

536
00:48:22.625 --> 00:48:25.167
and what adventure did he have?

537
00:48:27.292 --> 00:48:28.833
What did he bring in?

538
00:48:29.708 --> 00:48:32.458
Captain. that's the weird thing.

539
00:48:32.917 --> 00:48:34.583
The truck was
full of US dollars.

540
00:48:34.875 --> 00:48:36.000
US dollars?

541
00:48:36.833 --> 00:48:37.833
How much?

542
00:48:38.750 --> 00:48:40.958
It was quite a bit.

543
00:48:41.333 --> 00:48:44.417
About 20 bags full of them.

544
00:48:45.000 --> 00:48:48.042
But why do you think
those idiotic wild dogs

545
00:48:48.125 --> 00:48:51.292
were transporting
completely useless money?

546
00:48:54.042 --> 00:48:55.292
Where is it now?

547
00:48:56.542 --> 00:48:58.333
So they took the truck.

548
00:48:59.083 --> 00:49:00.333
What about the satellite phone?

549
00:49:01.125 --> 00:49:03.167
It should be by
the driver's seat.

550
00:49:11.625 --> 00:49:14.667
Sir. I'm not from here!

551
00:49:15.875 --> 00:49:17.958
I'm from Hong Kong!

552
00:49:19.875 --> 00:49:20.958
This is brand new.

553
00:49:21.042 --> 00:49:22.833
It's rare. Today
is your lucky day.

554
00:49:22.917 --> 00:49:24.125
Got anything else?

555
00:49:24.375 --> 00:49:25.375
I have...

556
00:49:25.750 --> 00:49:27.375
a satellite phone!

557
00:49:28.458 --> 00:49:31.750
With a satellite phone.
we can all get out of here!

558
00:49:32.667 --> 00:49:34.208
- Show us!
- Right here!

559
00:49:34.583 --> 00:49:36.917
- You lying sack of shit!
- He doesn't have it!

560
00:49:42.000 --> 00:49:44.500
Where do you think they
were heading with this money?

561
00:49:51.792 --> 00:49:53.500
Sir. where's the truck?

562
00:49:54.750 --> 00:49:56.083
Stop that!

563
00:49:56.417 --> 00:49:57.667
Stop! Please!

564
00:49:59.708 --> 00:50:01.250
Ah...

565
00:50:09.333 --> 00:50:10.417
He's really fresh!

566
00:50:10.500 --> 00:50:13.583
This guy's in good
shape. He's a Grade A!

567
00:50:17.125 --> 00:50:18.250
Can you run well?

568
00:50:18.833 --> 00:50:19.833
No?

569
00:50:23.042 --> 00:50:24.208
What should his number be?

570
00:50:24.292 --> 00:50:25.583
Give him Park Chan-ho's number.

571
00:50:25.667 --> 00:50:26.667
Number 61!

572
00:50:26.750 --> 00:50:28.083
Number 61 it is!

573
00:50:28.167 --> 00:50:30.042
Major League pitcher!

574
00:50:32.792 --> 00:50:33.917
That's a great number!

575
00:50:38.792 --> 00:50:39.917
Turn around!

576
00:50:42.875 --> 00:50:45.250
I'm betting a
chocolate bar on him.

577
00:50:50.417 --> 00:50:52.500
Sir. where's the truck?

578
00:51:04.458 --> 00:51:07.750
Sir! I'm not from here!

579
00:51:08.375 --> 00:51:10.333
There's money in the
truck! Go check it out!

580
00:51:10.417 --> 00:51:13.292
We can all leave if we
have that. you idiots!

581
00:51:34.042 --> 00:51:35.292
What...

582
00:51:40.583 --> 00:51:41.375
Hello?

583
00:51:41.376 --> 00:51:43.042
Where are you? The sun is out.

584
00:51:43.333 --> 00:51:44.667
What's going on?

585
00:51:45.958 --> 00:51:48.125
Hello. Who are you?

586
00:51:48.417 --> 00:51:49.417
What?

587
00:51:49.500 --> 00:51:50.792
Who the hell are you?

588
00:51:50.958 --> 00:51:52.208
Where's the money?

589
00:52:18.542 --> 00:52:19.750
Where are you going?

590
00:52:20.833 --> 00:52:22.167
I don't think we
should go out...

591
00:52:25.833 --> 00:52:27.917
Number 61! Get out!

592
00:52:29.583 --> 00:52:31.042
Get the hell out!

593
00:53:04.250 --> 00:53:05.625
I don't care who you are.

594
00:53:05.667 --> 00:53:06.833
Just bring the money.

595
00:53:06.917 --> 00:53:09.208
The terms are the same
as the guys we sent in...

596
00:53:09.458 --> 00:53:12.625
Half the money to anyone
that brings it out. Okay?

597
00:53:13.333 --> 00:53:16.708
Are you saying we
can get out of here?

598
00:53:16.792 --> 00:53:18.667
We are waiting
around Incheon Port.

599
00:53:18.750 --> 00:53:20.292
You call me when you get there.

600
00:53:20.958 --> 00:53:22.000
It's so easy!

601
00:53:22.792 --> 00:53:25.042
Easy. easy. I can
do it. I can do it.

602
00:53:25.125 --> 00:53:26.167
All right.

603
00:53:33.667 --> 00:53:35.167
You can drive. right?

604
00:53:36.333 --> 00:53:38.333
Let's just go now. Mom.

605
00:53:39.292 --> 00:53:41.292
I'll bulldoze them
all with my car.

606
00:53:43.917 --> 00:53:47.000
You'll just go in there?
In broad daylight?

607
00:55:01.625 --> 00:55:03.875
Run faster!

608
00:55:23.417 --> 00:55:27.417
It's time for us To say goodbye

609
00:55:27.792 --> 00:55:30.250
Let's meet again soon

610
00:55:31.750 --> 00:55:35.750
It's time for us To say goodbye

611
00:55:36.083 --> 00:55:38.667
Let's meet again soon

612
00:55:41.375 --> 00:55:42.583
Hey. buddy!

613
00:55:43.792 --> 00:55:45.417
If you don't hurry.
the doors will shut!

614
00:56:12.667 --> 00:56:13.917
You must be tired.

615
00:56:14.083 --> 00:56:15.333
You did great.

616
00:56:15.417 --> 00:56:16.792
How about a feast?

617
00:56:17.000 --> 00:56:18.417
You want it? Really?

618
00:56:19.542 --> 00:56:21.208
Have some ramen!

619
00:56:21.625 --> 00:56:23.875
Eat slowly! Share
them with your friends!

620
00:56:23.958 --> 00:56:25.250
Greedy bastards.

621
00:56:30.458 --> 00:56:31.583
You should share them!

622
00:56:33.542 --> 00:56:36.833
It's too dangerous now.
Let's move after sundown.

623
00:56:36.917 --> 00:56:39.583
I think we can go now. though...

624
00:56:40.458 --> 00:56:42.042
Go? Go where?

625
00:56:43.417 --> 00:56:45.833
Grandpa. we're
moving. Let's pack up.

626
00:56:46.125 --> 00:56:47.167
Move?

627
00:56:47.708 --> 00:56:48.708
Where?

628
00:56:48.792 --> 00:56:50.500
We're going to Incheon Port.

629
00:56:50.583 --> 00:56:52.263
Incheon Port? Are we
going to ride a boat?

630
00:56:52.292 --> 00:56:53.292
Okay!

631
00:56:53.375 --> 00:56:54.500
No. no. no!

632
00:56:54.917 --> 00:56:58.292
We must stay here until
Jane comes to rescue us.

633
00:56:58.375 --> 00:57:00.167
It was so hard convincing her!

634
00:57:00.250 --> 00:57:02.917
If Major Jane is coming.
tell her to come to the port.

635
00:57:03.000 --> 00:57:04.333
No way!

636
00:57:04.417 --> 00:57:05.792
You said you two are close.

637
00:57:06.583 --> 00:57:08.125
I guess you aren't.

638
00:57:08.917 --> 00:57:09.917
We're close.

639
00:57:10.125 --> 00:57:11.917
Okay. it's doable.

640
00:57:12.667 --> 00:57:14.125
Incheon? Incheon Port?

641
00:57:14.208 --> 00:57:16.292
- Grandpa. hurry!
- Okay.

642
00:57:18.875 --> 00:57:21.667
You'll take a crazy
old man and little kids

643
00:57:23.250 --> 00:57:25.708
to steal a truck
from armed soldiers?

644
00:57:26.708 --> 00:57:29.792
Then should I continue
living here with my girls?

645
00:57:31.167 --> 00:57:33.042
If you're scared. stay here.

646
00:57:34.708 --> 00:57:36.388
I'll give you this
place at a cheap price.

647
00:57:38.625 --> 00:57:40.333
Get him a first aid kit.

648
00:57:41.167 --> 00:57:43.292
and get some sleep.
We'll leave after sundown.

649
00:58:03.000 --> 00:58:04.542
Why did you save me earlier?

650
00:58:05.875 --> 00:58:08.333
I was going to leave. but
she wanted to save you.

651
00:58:09.333 --> 00:58:11.125
Dad told us we
should help the weak

652
00:58:11.250 --> 00:58:13.125
before he went to heaven.

653
00:58:14.292 --> 00:58:16.167
You looked weak.

654
00:58:18.417 --> 00:58:20.375
Stop yapping and go to bed.

655
00:58:20.625 --> 00:58:21.292
No!

656
00:58:21.375 --> 00:58:23.458
I'm going to bed soon
too. so go to sleep!

657
00:58:23.542 --> 00:58:24.667
I don't want to!

658
00:58:25.083 --> 00:58:26.792
One! Two!

659
00:58:28.250 --> 00:58:29.375
She's always like that...

660
00:58:29.458 --> 00:58:31.000
She thinks she's so big now.

661
00:58:32.667 --> 00:58:34.250
Maybe we should've
left you there.

662
00:58:34.875 --> 00:58:36.583
You're complaining
when we saved you.

663
00:58:37.667 --> 00:58:39.125
You look like a zombie.

664
00:58:45.167 --> 00:58:47.500
Mm...

665
00:58:48.750 --> 00:58:50.833
How long does it take
to get to Incheon Port?

666
00:58:50.917 --> 00:58:52.237
If we find an
unobstructed route.

667
00:58:52.292 --> 00:58:53.667
it'll only take thirty minutes.

668
00:58:54.000 --> 00:58:55.958
Thirty minutes. thirty
minutes. thirty minutes...

669
00:58:56.917 --> 00:58:58.518
What about zombies?
Wouldn't it be dangerous?

670
00:58:58.542 --> 00:58:59.708
They bite and stuff.

671
00:58:59.792 --> 00:59:00.958
- Captain.
- Yes?

672
00:59:01.667 --> 00:59:03.458
We need to get out of here.

673
00:59:03.583 --> 00:59:05.458
Forget about the zombies!

674
00:59:06.375 --> 00:59:08.125
Should we bring Sergeant Hwang?

675
00:59:08.833 --> 00:59:11.375
He's more dangerous
than the zombies.

676
00:59:11.667 --> 00:59:12.458
You're right.

677
00:59:12.542 --> 00:59:15.083
I can keep the
gatekeepers off our backs.

678
00:59:15.667 --> 00:59:19.208
but sharp-witted Sergeant
Hwang might get suspicious.

679
00:59:21.125 --> 00:59:22.958
Yes. you're right.

680
00:59:24.000 --> 00:59:30.000
Then I just have to find a
way to distract him. right?

681
01:00:11.708 --> 01:00:13.250
Sir? Sir!

682
01:00:13.833 --> 01:00:16.167
Sir! Please!

683
01:00:16.708 --> 01:00:20.708
Sir! Please just take my girl!

684
01:00:24.208 --> 01:00:27.750
Jung-seok. why are
you the only one alive?

685
01:01:02.083 --> 01:01:03.292
Put it down.

686
01:01:04.708 --> 01:01:05.958
You'll drain the batteries.

687
01:01:10.458 --> 01:01:13.292
Did Major Jane say she's
coming to Incheon Port?

688
01:01:13.375 --> 01:01:14.458
Huh?

689
01:01:17.542 --> 01:01:20.500
She should. She has to.

690
01:01:22.833 --> 01:01:25.083
She better rescue
my little darlings.

691
01:01:25.542 --> 01:01:27.000
My treasures.

692
01:01:28.167 --> 01:01:29.875
Yu-jin and Joon-i.

693
01:01:31.083 --> 01:01:33.833
they're the beacon
of hope in this hell.

694
01:01:36.750 --> 01:01:41.917
I'll get them out of
this hell no matter what.

695
01:01:45.083 --> 01:01:47.792
Major Jane is coming. right?

696
01:02:09.458 --> 01:02:10.500
Are you okay?

697
01:02:11.625 --> 01:02:15.292
We stole these when we
fled. Take what you need.

698
01:02:18.625 --> 01:02:20.750
I actually saw you before.

699
01:02:21.542 --> 01:02:22.542
I...

700
01:02:23.125 --> 01:02:24.167
came across your family

701
01:02:24.250 --> 01:02:26.542
when I was fleeing
to board the ship.

702
01:02:28.250 --> 01:02:29.958
You begged me to take your girl.

703
01:02:34.750 --> 01:02:36.625
Why are you telling me that now?

704
01:02:38.042 --> 01:02:39.083
Because you feel guilty?

705
01:02:40.167 --> 01:02:41.375
There were 31 cars.

706
01:02:42.458 --> 01:02:44.333
There were 31 cars
that drove past us.

707
01:02:45.542 --> 01:02:47.458
I thought the first car
would stop to help us.

708
01:02:48.042 --> 01:02:49.417
Or maybe the next one...

709
01:02:53.708 --> 01:02:55.458
All 31 cars just drove by.

710
01:02:58.417 --> 01:03:00.125
You're indebted to my girls.

711
01:03:05.750 --> 01:03:08.083
Yu-jin. I'm buttoning
you up. Stand up straight!

712
01:03:09.208 --> 01:03:12.375
Are we going on a boat ride now?

713
01:03:12.458 --> 01:03:15.458
Yes. we just have
to get something first.

714
01:03:19.000 --> 01:03:20.333
What about my cars?

715
01:03:20.667 --> 01:03:23.167
No way. we can't take them all.

716
01:03:26.583 --> 01:03:27.958
Then just this one!

717
01:03:28.292 --> 01:03:29.333
Put it down.

718
01:03:29.417 --> 01:03:31.083
Please. just one!

719
01:03:31.792 --> 01:03:33.417
Let me take one!

720
01:03:36.958 --> 01:03:38.000
Let's go.

721
01:04:28.542 --> 01:04:29.625
Joon-i.

722
01:04:30.375 --> 01:04:34.458
Stay here. If I'm not back
by sunrise. head back home.

723
01:04:35.083 --> 01:04:36.250
Just the three of us?

724
01:04:37.000 --> 01:04:38.208
What about you?

725
01:04:38.792 --> 01:04:40.083
How will you come home?

726
01:04:41.042 --> 01:04:42.917
I'll find my way somehow.

727
01:04:43.042 --> 01:04:44.792
so don't worry and head home.

728
01:04:46.708 --> 01:04:51.167
And don't ever
leave the car. got it?

729
01:04:53.208 --> 01:04:54.208
Answer me.

730
01:04:56.375 --> 01:04:57.375
Okay.

731
01:04:59.375 --> 01:05:00.833
Yu-jin. come here.

732
01:05:04.708 --> 01:05:08.917
I'll be back soon. Listen
to your sister. okay?

733
01:05:09.333 --> 01:05:11.292
You'll really be
back soon. right?

734
01:05:11.583 --> 01:05:12.958
Of course. I'll be right back.

735
01:05:25.375 --> 01:05:28.500
Commander. take
good care of my girls.

736
01:05:33.625 --> 01:05:34.667
Let's go.

737
01:06:36.375 --> 01:06:37.809
It's an emergency
exit that we found

738
01:06:37.833 --> 01:06:38.875
when we lived here.

739
01:07:14.583 --> 01:07:15.792
What the hell?

740
01:07:33.792 --> 01:07:34.875
Is that it?

741
01:07:38.375 --> 01:07:39.875
Yes. that's the one.

742
01:07:41.292 --> 01:07:42.458
Let's move quickly.

743
01:07:45.958 --> 01:07:47.792
Ah. ah. ah.

744
01:07:47.875 --> 01:07:50.542
I brought good news.

745
01:07:52.583 --> 01:07:58.708
Last night. the third platoon
led by Sergeant Hwang

746
01:07:58.792 --> 01:08:00.250
brought home a truck.

747
01:08:00.875 --> 01:08:05.125
There was enough
food for everyone to eat

748
01:08:05.208 --> 01:08:06.750
for an entire month.

749
01:08:11.750 --> 01:08:13.792
You've worked so
hard. I know you did!

750
01:08:13.875 --> 01:08:15.958
So tonight...

751
01:08:16.500 --> 01:08:18.917
there'll be an unlimited game

752
01:08:19.000 --> 01:08:20.708
for 24 hours!

753
01:08:23.083 --> 01:08:25.708
And remember.

754
01:08:26.167 --> 01:08:28.333
Have fun like
there's no tomorrow.

755
01:08:28.458 --> 01:08:29.625
Have a great time!

756
01:08:33.667 --> 01:08:36.792
There will be no tomorrow.

757
01:08:37.083 --> 01:08:40.833
Stop cheering. Doesn't
he seem strange?

758
01:08:40.958 --> 01:08:42.083
I think he's high.

759
01:08:42.167 --> 01:08:44.625
I'm not sure. Let's enjoy this!

760
01:08:49.542 --> 01:08:52.083
Hey. look over there.

761
01:08:52.625 --> 01:08:53.750
Shouldn't we report that?

762
01:08:54.250 --> 01:08:57.250
There aren't that many.
Why bother reporting?

763
01:08:58.083 --> 01:08:59.375
Forget it. don't mind them.

764
01:09:33.708 --> 01:09:34.833
Listen.

765
01:09:35.625 --> 01:09:37.375
Since you owe my girls.

766
01:09:38.833 --> 01:09:40.833
do me a favor later.

767
01:09:55.250 --> 01:09:59.000
Johnnie Walker Black Label!

768
01:10:02.167 --> 01:10:03.458
You're back.

769
01:10:04.833 --> 01:10:08.458
Are you supposed
to have booze here?

770
01:10:08.542 --> 01:10:09.583
Well...

771
01:10:09.833 --> 01:10:13.208
The game is about to
start. What brings you here?

772
01:10:13.292 --> 01:10:16.167
I haven't seen
your face in ages.

773
01:10:17.042 --> 01:10:20.125
Could I have a sip?

774
01:10:20.208 --> 01:10:21.542
Sure. help yourself.

775
01:10:21.625 --> 01:10:22.792
- Really?
- Sure.

776
01:10:23.833 --> 01:10:26.083
So why are you here?

777
01:10:26.250 --> 01:10:28.542
Do you have something to report?

778
01:10:28.625 --> 01:10:33.042
No. I was just curious what
gets you up in the morning.

779
01:10:35.667 --> 01:10:36.667
Hm?

780
01:10:43.333 --> 01:10:44.375
It's good?

781
01:10:44.583 --> 01:10:45.833
So good!

782
01:10:47.708 --> 01:10:51.000
If you love it that much.
you can take the bottle.

783
01:10:51.583 --> 01:10:52.833
It's my gift to you.

784
01:10:54.625 --> 01:10:56.375
- What's with you?
- What?

785
01:10:57.458 --> 01:10:59.458
I begged for some
snacks for my boys

786
01:10:59.542 --> 01:11:00.625
to boost morale.

787
01:11:00.708 --> 01:11:02.458
but all we got were scraps.

788
01:11:03.458 --> 01:11:05.042
You were acting so cheap.

789
01:11:06.875 --> 01:11:08.583
So why the sudden generosity?

790
01:11:09.750 --> 01:11:12.292
I think I told everyone
with my speech earlier.

791
01:11:13.208 --> 01:11:17.625
We owe so much to
you and your men...

792
01:11:17.708 --> 01:11:18.750
Bullshit!

793
01:11:22.167 --> 01:11:25.375
I was just kidding.

794
01:11:26.583 --> 01:11:30.542
Captain Seo. are you
hiding something from me?

795
01:11:32.542 --> 01:11:34.417
No. of course not.

796
01:11:37.667 --> 01:11:38.917
Captain Seo. I...

797
01:11:41.583 --> 01:11:42.667
Private Kim?

798
01:11:44.042 --> 01:11:46.708
Do you visit Captain
Seo's quarters frequently?

799
01:11:48.458 --> 01:11:50.917
No... I do not.

800
01:12:15.292 --> 01:12:17.708
Ah.

801
01:12:19.458 --> 01:12:20.625
You two are a thing?

802
01:12:22.167 --> 01:12:23.833
- Yes.
- My apologies!

803
01:12:26.292 --> 01:12:28.792
I'm so clueless.

804
01:12:29.625 --> 01:12:30.750
I'll leave you two alone.

805
01:12:31.917 --> 01:12:33.042
Just the two of you...

806
01:12:33.125 --> 01:12:35.333
Hm?

807
01:12:36.125 --> 01:12:39.417
I'll tell the boys to
avoid dropping in.

808
01:12:39.500 --> 01:12:40.667
so have a great time.

809
01:12:40.750 --> 01:12:44.250
Have a hot time. okay?

810
01:12:44.958 --> 01:12:46.000
All right.

811
01:12:46.792 --> 01:12:48.750
Love. love is...

812
01:12:50.667 --> 01:12:52.875
Sir. the preparation is done.
Shall we get to the truck?

813
01:12:52.958 --> 01:12:55.333
You go ahead. I have
something to do first.

814
01:12:55.417 --> 01:12:56.417
Yes. sir.

815
01:12:58.625 --> 01:13:00.750
Does he have a
death wish or what?

816
01:13:11.292 --> 01:13:14.833
Joon-i. look up ahead! Quickly!

817
01:13:24.792 --> 01:13:25.917
It's a march.

818
01:13:35.667 --> 01:13:38.000
That road is too
close to Unit 631.

819
01:13:38.083 --> 01:13:39.792
Aren't we going to go greet Mom?

820
01:14:11.500 --> 01:14:12.708
The money is intact.

821
01:14:34.833 --> 01:14:37.833
Hey. can't you take me with you?

822
01:14:38.500 --> 01:14:39.958
I really want to
get out of here.

823
01:14:41.208 --> 01:14:43.583
Go where? Who
told you about that?

824
01:14:44.542 --> 01:14:47.500
I overheard Captain Seo
talking on the satellite phone.

825
01:14:48.250 --> 01:14:49.667
Please take me with you.

826
01:14:50.083 --> 01:14:51.417
Satellite phone?

827
01:14:52.042 --> 01:14:53.333
Where did you get it?

828
01:14:53.708 --> 01:14:56.125
The wild dog we
found in the truck had it.

829
01:14:56.958 --> 01:14:58.125
Private Kim!

830
01:14:58.208 --> 01:14:59.708
Aren't you going
to see the game?

831
01:15:01.083 --> 01:15:02.500
Answer naturally.

832
01:15:05.625 --> 01:15:06.792
I'm all right.

833
01:15:07.292 --> 01:15:08.958
You always say that. Oh. right.

834
01:15:09.375 --> 01:15:11.958
That wild dog who
came with the truck.

835
01:15:12.042 --> 01:15:13.667
that guy was no joke.

836
01:15:14.042 --> 01:15:17.292
He was struggling
so much to survive.

837
01:15:18.458 --> 01:15:20.375
I bet all my canned
goods on him!

838
01:15:21.250 --> 01:15:22.333
I'll see you later.

839
01:15:24.083 --> 01:15:25.667
Where is the phone now?

840
01:15:25.875 --> 01:15:27.625
It's not with me.

841
01:15:27.708 --> 01:15:29.292
Captain Seo has it.
He'll be here soon.

842
01:15:33.417 --> 01:15:34.625
Get going.

843
01:15:35.667 --> 01:15:36.958
I can't wait long.

844
01:15:43.333 --> 01:15:46.375
Act naturally when that
bastard comes. got it?

845
01:15:48.000 --> 01:15:49.083
Okay...

846
01:15:50.583 --> 01:15:53.042
Number 61!

847
01:16:15.667 --> 01:16:17.042
What are you doing? Let's move!

848
01:16:19.000 --> 01:16:20.292
Captain...

849
01:16:21.750 --> 01:16:23.292
Long time no see. Captain Seo.

850
01:16:25.000 --> 01:16:27.167
Min-jung. you were alive. Gosh.

851
01:16:28.208 --> 01:16:30.000
You have the
satellite phone. right?

852
01:16:30.375 --> 01:16:31.458
Hand it over.

853
01:16:33.167 --> 01:16:34.417
The satellite phone...

854
01:16:35.083 --> 01:16:36.208
Give me a second.

855
01:16:37.042 --> 01:16:38.625
Mm. Oh.

856
01:16:52.375 --> 01:16:53.417
Wasn't that a gunshot?

857
01:16:53.500 --> 01:16:55.309
Like hell it was. Just
shut up and eat this tuna.

858
01:16:55.333 --> 01:16:56.375
Hey!

859
01:17:01.625 --> 01:17:02.625
Oh.

860
01:17:04.792 --> 01:17:05.875
Let's go get Mom.

861
01:17:22.833 --> 01:17:24.625
Look! That bastard!

862
01:17:29.500 --> 01:17:30.958
Gun! Get the guns!

863
01:17:34.542 --> 01:17:36.250
- Are you okay?
- Yes...

864
01:17:37.042 --> 01:17:38.083
Can you get up?

865
01:17:38.375 --> 01:17:40.292
Yes. I can get up. I can get up.

866
01:17:47.625 --> 01:17:48.875
Stay behind me.

867
01:17:51.500 --> 01:17:53.875
Hey. where did he go?

868
01:17:54.208 --> 01:17:55.208
Jesus Christ...

869
01:17:57.458 --> 01:18:00.667
Min-jung. I was so worried...

870
01:18:02.750 --> 01:18:04.667
That's mine. give it back...

871
01:18:08.542 --> 01:18:09.583
Sergeant!

872
01:18:11.625 --> 01:18:13.292
Where did that bastard go?

873
01:18:17.583 --> 01:18:18.792
Go look for him.

874
01:18:26.250 --> 01:18:27.417
Block the entrance!

875
01:18:31.583 --> 01:18:32.625
Move!

876
01:19:22.542 --> 01:19:23.750
Fire! Fire!

877
01:19:50.833 --> 01:19:52.208
Hey. Go forward.

878
01:20:21.333 --> 01:20:22.333
Damn it!

879
01:20:22.500 --> 01:20:23.500
Jung-seok!

880
01:20:39.333 --> 01:20:40.417
Sergeant!

881
01:21:24.417 --> 01:21:25.625
Come on!

882
01:22:09.750 --> 01:22:12.333
Hurry! Get in!

883
01:22:16.958 --> 01:22:18.833
Get in! Come on!

884
01:22:23.042 --> 01:22:24.417
Snap out of it!

885
01:22:25.125 --> 01:22:26.375
Come on!

886
01:22:27.792 --> 01:22:28.875
Hurry!

887
01:22:49.250 --> 01:22:52.250
Go after them!

888
01:23:07.000 --> 01:23:08.792
Captain. are you okay?

889
01:23:11.917 --> 01:23:13.083
What do we do now. sir?

890
01:23:16.375 --> 01:23:17.458
Captain!

891
01:23:25.708 --> 01:23:27.375
You did all you can.

892
01:23:27.875 --> 01:23:29.167
That's what matters.

893
01:23:29.500 --> 01:23:30.625
Get it together.

894
01:23:55.542 --> 01:23:56.625
Sergeant Hwang!

895
01:23:58.625 --> 01:23:59.708
Step on it!

896
01:24:03.042 --> 01:24:06.875
It's time for us To say goodbye

897
01:24:07.500 --> 01:24:09.542
Let's meet again soon

898
01:25:23.458 --> 01:25:24.542
Grandpa. hurry!

899
01:25:24.917 --> 01:25:26.292
Okay!

900
01:25:29.708 --> 01:25:30.958
Open the window.

901
01:25:54.208 --> 01:25:55.583
Mom!

902
01:25:56.083 --> 01:25:58.708
We came to greet you!

903
01:25:58.792 --> 01:26:01.042
Why don't you ever listen to me?

904
01:26:02.292 --> 01:26:03.417
Come on!

905
01:26:17.417 --> 01:26:18.625
Yee-haw!

906
01:26:43.875 --> 01:26:44.917
Hold on.

907
01:26:45.000 --> 01:26:46.000
Okay!

908
01:27:14.917 --> 01:27:20.000
Hey! Stop with the damn
flares! Just kill them all!

909
01:27:39.917 --> 01:27:41.042
They're behind us!

910
01:27:47.417 --> 01:27:48.583
Hold on tight!

911
01:28:02.083 --> 01:28:03.292
Come on!

912
01:28:13.333 --> 01:28:15.250
You asshole!

913
01:28:23.542 --> 01:28:24.750
He's not bad.

914
01:29:11.167 --> 01:29:13.125
Pull up closer. asshole!

915
01:29:13.208 --> 01:29:14.625
This way. move up!

916
01:29:15.792 --> 01:29:16.792
Kill him!

917
01:29:32.292 --> 01:29:33.917
Watch the front. asshole!

918
01:29:34.458 --> 01:29:35.500
Hold the wheel!

919
01:29:37.208 --> 01:29:38.208
Hey!

920
01:29:48.417 --> 01:29:49.500
Turn on the lights.

921
01:30:15.167 --> 01:30:16.417
To our right!

922
01:30:33.208 --> 01:30:34.250
Beside you!

923
01:30:58.417 --> 01:30:59.417
Watch out!

924
01:31:44.833 --> 01:31:45.958
Hold on tight!

925
01:32:59.667 --> 01:33:01.000
Go over to the right!

926
01:33:32.208 --> 01:33:34.500
Hey! Back up. back up. back up!

927
01:33:40.250 --> 01:33:42.458
Back it up!

928
01:33:43.917 --> 01:33:46.833
I said back it up. asshole!

929
01:33:50.542 --> 01:33:52.333
Just step on it!

930
01:33:53.417 --> 01:33:55.750
Back the shit up!

931
01:33:56.542 --> 01:33:58.417
What the hell are
you doing? Back it up!

932
01:34:02.500 --> 01:34:03.583
You bastard!

933
01:34:29.667 --> 01:34:30.958
We're almost there.

934
01:34:41.125 --> 01:34:42.458
We arrive at Incheon Port

935
01:34:42.500 --> 01:34:43.792
in 15 minutes.

936
01:35:18.958 --> 01:35:19.958
Joon-i.

937
01:35:20.583 --> 01:35:23.375
Is that the boat? Oh. yes!

938
01:35:34.542 --> 01:35:35.583
Yu-jin...

939
01:35:36.375 --> 01:35:37.500
Yu-jin. are you okay?

940
01:35:38.792 --> 01:35:39.833
Hi.

941
01:35:43.208 --> 01:35:44.208
Joon-i!

942
01:35:47.000 --> 01:35:49.417
Put down your gun! Come on!

943
01:35:51.417 --> 01:35:52.500
Drop it!

944
01:35:52.917 --> 01:35:55.042
Do you want to see
her head blown up?

945
01:35:55.125 --> 01:35:56.208
Put it down!

946
01:36:01.250 --> 01:36:03.667
Kick it! Kick it away!

947
01:36:04.583 --> 01:36:06.000
Yes. that's it.

948
01:36:10.000 --> 01:36:12.083
I can finally get
off this peninsula...

949
01:36:12.792 --> 01:36:15.958
When I leave. I'm
going to live to the fullest

950
01:36:16.042 --> 01:36:17.833
in Hong Kong.

951
01:36:20.208 --> 01:36:23.208
They won't know what I did here.

952
01:36:23.583 --> 01:36:25.542
I'm going to be a good man.

953
01:36:26.292 --> 01:36:29.708
Thank you. Thank you so much.

954
01:36:29.792 --> 01:36:31.375
I'll thank you every night.

955
01:36:31.833 --> 01:36:34.000
I really mean it.
Thank you so much.

956
01:36:34.083 --> 01:36:36.500
I love you all!

957
01:36:36.583 --> 01:36:37.583
Now!

958
01:36:40.583 --> 01:36:41.583
Okay...

959
01:36:47.667 --> 01:36:48.667
No!

960
01:37:20.000 --> 01:37:21.458
Grandpa...

961
01:37:22.417 --> 01:37:25.167
Grandpa. are you okay?

962
01:37:25.542 --> 01:37:26.792
Grandpa...

963
01:37:27.000 --> 01:37:28.583
Mom! Mom...

964
01:38:02.167 --> 01:38:03.250
The sun is rising.

965
01:38:03.333 --> 01:38:04.333
A horde's coming.

966
01:38:04.917 --> 01:38:06.083
We have to depart!

967
01:38:18.000 --> 01:38:19.083
The money's here.

968
01:38:22.375 --> 01:38:23.375
Huh?

969
01:38:24.458 --> 01:38:26.000
It's not him.

970
01:38:27.458 --> 01:38:29.167
How many times did they switch?

971
01:38:32.083 --> 01:38:33.292
Nice to meet you...

972
01:38:33.917 --> 01:38:36.125
- Nice to meet you too.
- Thank you.

973
01:38:43.667 --> 01:38:46.708
Get rid of the body!

974
01:39:00.917 --> 01:39:04.375
Hey. stop!

975
01:39:14.375 --> 01:39:17.292
Get the money!

976
01:39:17.375 --> 01:39:20.292
Shut the back hatch!
Zombies are coming!

977
01:39:52.917 --> 01:39:55.625
Grandpa...

978
01:39:58.333 --> 01:40:01.208
Okay. I'm okay...

979
01:40:01.708 --> 01:40:03.958
Grandpa...

980
01:40:07.792 --> 01:40:10.792
I wanted to pull
you out of this hell...

981
01:40:14.042 --> 01:40:15.208
No...

982
01:40:16.667 --> 01:40:19.375
We were together all along.

983
01:40:20.833 --> 01:40:22.833
Why would this be hell?

984
01:40:24.875 --> 01:40:25.917
Thank you...

985
01:40:26.833 --> 01:40:28.750
Grandpa...

986
01:40:32.792 --> 01:40:34.417
Grandpa!

987
01:40:36.000 --> 01:40:37.458
I'm sorry...

988
01:40:38.958 --> 01:40:41.250
for making you
live in this world...

989
01:40:41.625 --> 01:40:43.750
Grandpa...

990
01:40:45.375 --> 01:40:49.208
- Grandpa...
- I'm sorry...

991
01:40:49.458 --> 01:40:50.875
Grandpa.

992
01:40:56.458 --> 01:40:57.917
Grandpa!

993
01:41:03.042 --> 01:41:04.792
Don't die...

994
01:41:09.875 --> 01:41:12.583
Grandpa! No!

995
01:41:15.000 --> 01:41:16.542
Grandpa...

996
01:41:57.083 --> 01:41:58.792
Girls! The fireworks!

997
01:41:58.875 --> 01:41:59.917
Hurry!

998
01:42:01.375 --> 01:42:02.375
Joon-i!

999
01:42:08.958 --> 01:42:12.375
You promised to
do a favor for me.

1000
01:42:13.708 --> 01:42:16.667
Take the girls with
you no matter what.

1001
01:42:17.500 --> 01:42:18.542
Got it?

1002
01:42:18.875 --> 01:42:19.875
Promise me. okay?

1003
01:42:20.625 --> 01:42:21.667
Get going!

1004
01:42:22.458 --> 01:42:23.458
Now!

1005
01:42:37.875 --> 01:42:41.000
Commander. thank you.

1006
01:43:28.292 --> 01:43:30.542
Morn's falling behind!

1007
01:44:32.625 --> 01:44:33.792
Are you all right?

1008
01:44:34.000 --> 01:44:35.167
You're safe now!

1009
01:44:39.250 --> 01:44:39.917
Jane...

1010
01:44:40.000 --> 01:44:41.000
Jane!

1011
01:44:41.083 --> 01:44:44.042
Jane! We have to save my mom!

1012
01:44:44.125 --> 01:44:45.458
I'm sorry. It's too late!

1013
01:44:45.542 --> 01:44:46.750
We can't put you in danger.

1014
01:44:46.833 --> 01:44:47.917
We must leave now!

1015
01:44:48.000 --> 01:44:50.750
Please. help my mom!

1016
01:44:51.458 --> 01:44:52.958
Please! Just this once!

1017
01:44:53.125 --> 01:44:54.125
Go! Let's go!

1018
01:44:54.417 --> 01:44:55.417
Let's go!

1019
01:44:55.500 --> 01:44:56.667
You must wait!

1020
01:44:59.375 --> 01:45:00.417
Please...

1021
01:45:02.000 --> 01:45:03.958
Remain calm...

1022
01:45:14.333 --> 01:45:15.708
Don't wait for me...

1023
01:45:40.000 --> 01:45:41.000
No...

1024
01:45:42.417 --> 01:45:43.417
Mom!

1025
01:45:43.500 --> 01:45:46.292
Don't do it. Mom!

1026
01:45:55.708 --> 01:45:56.750
Let go of me!

1027
01:46:00.375 --> 01:46:01.375
Mom!

1028
01:46:10.500 --> 01:46:12.125
Mom. please!

1029
01:46:20.208 --> 01:46:23.000
She made a very
sensible decision.

1030
01:46:23.667 --> 01:46:27.542
It was for the best!
For everyone...

1031
01:46:28.667 --> 01:46:30.333
Sensible decision. my ass.

1032
01:46:32.375 --> 01:46:33.542
Did you even try?

1033
01:46:36.333 --> 01:46:37.333
Jung-seok...

1034
01:46:38.708 --> 01:46:40.208
You're tormented too!

1035
01:46:41.917 --> 01:46:43.250
You just gave up!

1036
01:46:43.333 --> 01:46:45.958
We have to save Mom!

1037
01:46:52.917 --> 01:46:54.500
I'll bring back your mom.

1038
01:46:55.708 --> 01:46:56.917
Wait right here.

1039
01:47:08.917 --> 01:47:11.125
Mom! Run!

1040
01:48:42.167 --> 01:48:44.542
- Mom!
- Mom!

1041
01:48:52.125 --> 01:48:53.125
Mom!

1042
01:50:10.042 --> 01:50:12.875
Don't worry. She'll be okay.

1043
01:50:17.625 --> 01:50:18.917
She'll be fine.

1044
01:50:32.750 --> 01:50:35.458
In a few hours. a new
world will be waiting.

1045
01:50:37.250 --> 01:50:41.000
The world I knew
wasn't bad either.

1046
01:55:33.958 --> 01:55:35.707
ALL CHARACTERS. PLACES.
ORGANIZATIONS. NAMES AND INCIDENTS

1047
01:55:35.708 --> 01:55:37.583
PORTRAYED IN THIS
FILM ARE FICTITIOUS
